    "body": "But the refinements need to be initialised at some point. In my specific use case, I initialise it when I click on it, however it changes when there is a change in the refinement. \n\nI havent quite got time to implement the solution as I know this solution will give me problems on the listing page as there will be refinements present on the url but none of the refinements would be mounted on the listing page since there is no space for filters. \n",
